 {"id":"bd-2g0","title":"[Net] Implement Unix Sockets (UnixListener, UnixStream, UnixDatagram)","description":"# Unix Socket Implementation

## Overview
Unix domain sockets for local IPC with cancel-correct operations.

## UnixListener

```rust
#[cfg(unix)]
pub struct UnixListener {
    inner: sys::UnixListener,
}

impl UnixListener {
    /// Bind to path
    pub fn bind(path: impl AsRef<Path>) -> io::Result<Self>;

    /// Bind to abstract address (Linux)
    #[cfg(target_os = "linux")]
    pub fn bind_abstract(name: &[u8]) -> io::Result<Self>;

    /// Accept connection
    pub async fn accept(&self) -> io::Result<(UnixStream, SocketAddr)>;

    /// Get local address
    pub fn local_addr(&self) -> io::Result<SocketAddr>;

    /// Incoming stream
    pub fn incoming(&self) -> Incoming<'_>;
}
```

## UnixStream

```rust
#[cfg(unix)]
pub struct UnixStream {
    inner: sys::UnixStream,
}

impl UnixStream {
    /// Connect to path
    pub async fn connect(path: impl AsRef<Path>) -> io::Result<Self>;

    /// Create connected pair
    pub fn pair() -> io::Result<(Self, Self)>;

    /// Get peer address
    pub fn peer_addr(&self) -> io::Result<SocketAddr>;

    /// Get local address
    pub fn local_addr(&self) -> io::Result<SocketAddr>;

    /// Get peer credentials
    pub fn peer_cred(&self) -> io::Result<UCred>;

    /// Split into halves
    pub fn split(&mut self) -> (ReadHalf<'_>, WriteHalf<'_>);
}

impl AsyncRead for UnixStream { ... }
impl AsyncWrite for UnixStream { ... }

/// Peer credentials
pub struct UCred {
    pub uid: u32,
    pub gid: u32,
    pub pid: Option<i32>,
}
```

## UnixDatagram

```rust
#[cfg(unix)]
pub struct UnixDatagram {
    inner: sys::UnixDatagram,
}

impl UnixDatagram {
    /// Bind to path
    pub fn bind(path: impl AsRef<Path>) -> io::Result<Self>;

    /// Create unbound socket
    pub fn unbound() -> io::Result<Self>;

    /// Create connected pair
    pub fn pair() -> io::Result<(Self, Self)>;

    /// Connect to path
    pub fn connect(&self, path: impl AsRef<Path>) -> io::Result<()>;

    /// Send to address
    pub async fn send_to(&self, buf: &[u8], path: impl AsRef<Path>) -> io::Result<usize>;

    /// Receive with source
    pub async fn recv_from(&self, buf: &mut [u8]) -> io::Result<(usize, SocketAddr)>;

    /// Send to connected
    pub async fn send(&self, buf: &[u8]) -> io::Result<usize>;

    /// Receive from connected
    pub async fn recv(&self, buf: &mut [u8]) -> io::Result<usize>;
}
```

## Ancillary Data (File Descriptor Passing)

```rust
/// Socket ancillary data
pub struct SocketAncillary<'a> {
    buffer: &'a mut [u8],
    length: usize,
}

impl SocketAncillary<'_> {
    /// Add file descriptors
    pub fn add_fds(&mut self, fds: &[RawFd]) -> bool;

    /// Iterate received messages
    pub fn messages(&self) -> impl Iterator<Item = AncillaryMessage<'_>>;
}

pub enum AncillaryMessage<'a> {
    ScmRights(&'a [RawFd]),
    ScmCredentials(UCred),
}

impl UnixStream {
    /// Send with ancillary data
    pub async fn send_with_ancillary(&self, buf: &[u8], ancillary: &mut SocketAncillary<'_>) -> io::Result<usize>;

    /// Receive with ancillary data
    pub async fn recv_with_ancillary(&self, buf: &mut [u8], ancillary: &mut SocketAncillary<'_>) -> io::Result<usize>;
}
```

## Testing
- stream connect/accept
- datagram send/recv
- socket pair
- file descriptor passing
- peer credentials
- abstract addresses (Linux)

